    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Dead Code in RU PRACH Thread Function\n\n### Summary\nThe `ru_thread_prach` function in `executables/lte-ru.c` contained dead code that was never executed and could mask intended logic downstream. The incorrect else branch has been removed to ensure proper PRACH processing flow.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-ru.c`: Removed dead else branch in `ru_thread_prach` function that called `rx_prach` with NULL parameters. The function now properly routes all PRACH processing through `prach_procedures` when `ru->eNB_list[0]` is present.\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, the dead code path could potentially be triggered in edge cases where RU initialization ordering is not properly handled, leading to:\n- Segmentation fault when `rx_prach` is called with NULL parameters\n- Incorrect PRACH processing due to missing preamble detection parameters\n- Deadlock conditions when mutexes are not properly released\n\nThe issue manifests when the PRACH thread starts before `ru->eNB_list[0]` is properly initialized, causing the incorrect code path to execute. This can be observed by monitoring the PRACH detection logs which would show no preamble detection activity.\n"
}